<title>HUNGARY: Gardenia Q1 97 after-tax profit rises to 96mln.</title>
<headline>Gardenia Q1 97 after-tax profit rises to 96mln.</headline>
<dateline>BUDAPEST 1997-05-15</dateline>
<text>
<p>Three-month period ending March 31.</p>
<p>(Figures in millions of forints unless stated)</p>
<p>					   Jan-March 1997  Jan-March 1996</p>
<p>    Group operating profit	     21	  vs	78</p>
<p>    Group pre-tax profit		112	  vs	43</p>
<p>    Group after-tax profit	     96	  vs	35</p>
<p>    Group net sales		     995	  vs     731</p>
<p>    Group other revenue		  11	  vs	21</p>
<p>    Direct costs of sales	    483	   vs    326</p>
<p>    Indirect costs of sales	  449	   vs    302</p>
<p>    Other expenditures		  53	   vs     46</p>
<p>    Net financial income	     182 profit  vs     34 loss</p>
<p>	Financial revenue		206	   vs	0</p>
<p>	Financial expenditure	   24	   vs     34</p>
<p>    Net extraordinary income	  91 loss    vs	1 loss</p>
<p>	Extraordinary revenue	    0	   vs	0</p>
<p>	Extraordinary expenditure     91	   vs	1</p>
<p>    Taxation				16	   vs	8</p>
<p>NOTE - Gardenia Rt is a curtain manufacturer. The figures are consolidated, unaudited and were calculated in accordance with Hungarian Accounting Standards.</p>
<p>-- Budapest newsroom +36 1 327-4040</p>
